    }
  ],
  "readiness": "NEEDS_REWORK",
  "summary": "The architectural direction is sound and all the round-1 nits were addressed, but five contract-level gaps remain that will cause review rework across SDK, daemon, and adapter implementations: undefined extension wire payload structs (`tools/call` / `provide_tools`), undefined schema-digest canonicalization, undefined remote-MCP bearer-injection interface, an internal contradiction in how the hosted MCP bind token traverses the ACP wire while being declared claim_token-equivalent, and an unbounded approval-bridge wait. Resolve B-001..B-005 with code-block-level edits and the TechSpec is ready for tasks; until then it would force exactly the multi-round trajectory L-012 warns against."
